Lieutenant General Robert Kibochi was on Wednesday named Vice Chief of Defence Forces replacing Lieutenant General Joseph Kasaon. The changes by President Uhuru Kenyatta are yet to be announced. Major General Walter Raria will take over from Kibochi as Kenya Army Commander. Kibochi was promoted in readiness to replace General Samson Mwathethe at the end of his term. The CDF's office is rotational in the tri-service. It is nowÂ Kenya Army's turn to lead after the exit of Mwathethe of Kenya Navy. Kenya Navy's Major General AS Farah was named the Director of Military Intelligence (DMI) replacing Major General Charles Mwai. Farah will undergo a year's training abroad before taking office. He is the second Kenya Navy staffer to head military intelligence after retired Chief of General Staff Joseph Kibwana. Mwai took over as the Chief of Military Intelligence in September 2014, replacing National Intelligence Service boss Major General Philip Kameru. Major General Thomas Chepkuto, the head of Special Programmes at the Defence Headquarters, will hold the office of the DMI in the meantime. KDF spokesman Colonel David Obonyo was promoted to the senior rank of brigadier and appointed the deputy DMI. He will be replaced by his deputy Lieutenant Colonel Paul Njunguna. Click here for the latest political news  